joseph hui transformative learning technologies laboratory home about publications projects people teaching media fablearn 2011 home people joseph hui joseph hui position high school interns joseph is a senior at cupertino high school and spent the summer of 2011 as an intern at the tltlab during his time at the lab joseph learned about electronics and programming microprocessors specifically the pic the type of microprocessor used in the gogo board he worked on creating an educational device for the lab developing the sensor pen a small inexpensive way for students to explore the world around them he is currently working with others including tltlab students anna ly and stellios leventis to refine the sensor pen and prepare it for mass production joseph hopes to major in computer science in college people faculty visiting researchers phd students ma students ms students undergraduate students high school interns collaborators alumni transformative learning technologies lab school of education stanford university 520 galvez mall room 102 ceras building stanford california 94305 usa connect with us connect with us on facebook connect with us on twitter connect with us on youtube connect with us on flickr copyright 2011 all rights reserved top
